text:
Ellsworth County (county code EW) is a county in the U.S. state of Kansas. In 2010, 6,497 people lived there. Its county seat is Ellsworth. Ellsworth is also the biggest city in the county.
Geography.
The U.S. Census Bureau says that the county has a total area of. Of that, is land and (1.0%) is water. It is intersected by the Smoky Hill River.
